com.github.basking2.sdsai

Class ArrayTree<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.basking2.sdsai.ArrayTree<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class ArrayTree<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
    A tree backed by an array. Because this tree is backed by an array, the tree is full. That is to say, when you iterate over it, every node value will be handed back whether it is defined or null. The user of this should take care to filter out values they do not want or consider undefined.
